org.sbolstandard.core2

Class SequenceOntology

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbolstandard.core2.SequenceOntology

  • public class SequenceOntology
extends Object
    This class provides methods for accessing Sequence Ontology (SO) terms and querying about their relationships.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Zhen Zhang, Tramy Nguyen, Nicholas Roehner, Chris Myers

      • getId

        public final String getId(String stanzaName)
        Returns the ID of the stanza whose name matches the given stanza name. If multiple matches are found, only the first matching one is returned.
        Parameters:
        stanzaName - the name of a stanza
        Returns:
        the matching stanza ID, or null if no match is found.

      • getURIbyName

        public final URI getURIbyName(String stanzaName)
        Returns the URI, i.e. the Sequence Ontology (SO) namespace, i.e. "http://identifiers.org/so/", followed by the ID of an SO term, of the term whose name matches the given name. If multiple matches are found, only the first matching one is returned.
        Parameters:
        stanzaName - the name of a term
        Returns:
        the URI of the given SO name.

        Returns:

      • isDescendantOf

        public final boolean isDescendantOf(URI childURI,
                     URI parentURI)
        Returns true if the term with childURI is a descendant of the term with parentURI. This method first extracts IDs for the child and parent terms, and then pass them to isDescendantOf(String, String).
        Parameters:
        childURI - the URI of the child term
        parentURI - the URI of the parent term
        Returns:
        true if the term with childURI is a descendant of the term with parentURI, false otherwise.
